  "body": "- [x] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nA fresh truffle init will default to using Solidity v0.5.16, which is almost 2 years old.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\ntruffle init\r\ntruffle compile\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTruffle should compile with a version of `solc` that is current.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\n> Compiled successfully using:\r\n   - solc: 0.5.16\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Potential Solution\r\n\r\nChanging the default would break Truffle projects in the wild and force developers to migrate their projects, which is unacceptable.  Instead, running `truffle init` could provide a current version within `truffle-config.js` so that new projects aren't relying on truffle's outdated default.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macOS Big Sur, 11.6\r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.4.11 (core: 5.4.11)\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v16.0.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 7.10.0",
