    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "One approach I've had in mind for this is that we can create a user-level config (`~/.config/truffle/...`) parameter called \"default Solidity version\" and use that moving forward. This parameter would control the default at the project-level (`truffle-config.js`), so users could configure Truffle \"globally\" to set their preferred default for all projects moving forward. This would not be breaking, because the default user-level default would remain 0.5.16, but we could encourage people to upgrade this way.",
